    "body": "API:\n\n``` go\nfunc (b *BlockPool) Status() *Status \n```\n\nStatus is reporting about the BlockPool. Cumulative counts report over the period of this session (since start of the blockpool = launch of client)\n\nStatus Public Fields:\n\n``` go\nSyncing           bool   // true if requesting, updating etc, false if idle\n\nBlockHashes       int    // number of hashes fetched \nBlockHashesInPool int    // number of hashes currently in the pool\nBlocks            int    // number of blocks fetched \nBlocksInPool      int    // number of blocks currently in the pool\nBlocksInChain     int    // number of blocks inserted/connected to the blockchain ()\nNewBlocks         int    // number of new blocks (received with new blocks msg) \nForks             int    // number of chain forks in the blockpool \nLongestChain      int    // the longest chain inserted (aka session blockchain height)\n\nPeers             int    // cumulative number of all different registered peers\nActivePeers       int    // cumulative number of all different peers that contributed a hash or block \nLivePeers         int    // number of live peers registered with the block pool (supposed to be redundant but good sanity check\nBestPeers         int    // cumulative number of all peers that at some point were promoted as best peer (peer with highest TD status) \nBadPeers          int    // cumulative number of all peers that violated the protocol (invalid block or pow, unrequested hash or block, etc)\n```\n",
